40. If an officer is found guilty of a disciplinary offence, any one or any
combination of two or more of the following punishments, depending upon the
seriousness of the offence, may be imposed on the officer:
(a) warning;
(b) fine;
(c) forfeiture of emoluments;
(d) deferment of salary movement;
Statutory Bodies (Discipline and Surcharge)                   41
(e) reduction of salary;
(f) reduction in rank;
(g) dismissal.
